main event: Numerous bright lights were observed in the night sky over Phoenix, Arizona, on March 3, 1966.
interesting points: Witnesses reported glowing and pulsating lights to the southwest of Phoenix,The objects were stationary at an estimated altitude of 2000 to 3000 feet,The lights moved in a southerly direction while maintaining a stationary posture,No sound was reported by the witnesses,Photographic evidence in the form of 8mm movie film was obtained during the incident.
witness description: various witnesses from the Phoenix metropolitan area
